ins 90.1% along with good Faradaic efficiency of 98.6%, demonstrating the good cycling durability of the device. The fitted EIS plot of the corresponding device with equivalent circuit demonstrates the lower Rct of the device, indicating the good ionic as well as electrochemical kinetics of the device, as presented in the inset of Fig. 6h. Overall, the proposed dual-layered NCM-based MOF-5//N–O AC device and its obtained energy storage properties pave a new method for gaining superior energy storage for practical applications.Fig. 6
